author: maxb
msg: SWIG/Python: Declare the package in the SWIG %module line.
Change is a no-op for now, but will matter in the future when
PEP 328 DeprecationWarnings get turned on in Python 2.6.
[in subversion/bindings/swig/]
* core.i, svn_client.i, svn_delta.i, svn_fs.i, svn_ra.i, svn_repos.i, svn_wc.i

author: maxb
msg: SWIG: Auth prompting refactoring.
[in subversion/bindings/swig/]
* include/svn_types.swg: Move the Ruby CALLBACK_BATON typemap out of here,
to svn_client.i, which is the only place it is applied.
* svn_client.i: Ruby CALLBACK_BATON typemap moved here.
Big FIXME comment added questioning much about CALLBACK_BATON typemaps.
Move out the auth prompting typemaps to core.i, since they need to apply to
things in the svn_auth namespace as well as just the svn_client one now.
* core.i: Macro-ized auth prompting typemaps moved here, subsuming the
explicitly written out Ruby ones already present.
